The equation used depends on the specific scenario and requirements outlined in the regulations. The use of Tier 1 or 2 is permitted, and the choice is based on the criteria described in paragraphs (b)(1)(iii), (b)(1)(v), (b)(1)(viii), and (b)(2)(ii) of the section. The calculation involves counting all major equipment listed in Table W–1B and Table W–1C, and then multiplying the major equipment counts by the average component counts listed in the respective tables. The appropriate factor in Table W–1A is used for operations in Eastern and Western U.S. based on the mapping in Table W–1D. The specific equations and methods for calculating emissions are determined based on the type of facility, equipment, and geographic location, as detailed in the regulations.{
