Equation W-10A or W-10B was used for the calculation of annual volumetric total gas emissions from well venting during completions and workovers involving hydraulic fracturing. Equation W-10A applies when the gas flowback rate is measured from a specified number of example completions or workovers, while Equation W-10B applies when the gas flowback vent or flare volume is measured for each completion or workover. The emissions must be calculated separately for completions and workovers, for each sub-basin, and for each well type combination identified in paragraph (g)(2) of this section. When making gas flowback measurements for use in Equations W–12A and W–12B of this section, a recording flow meter (digital or analog) installed on the vent line, downstream of a separator and ahead of a flare or vent, must be used to measure the gas flowback rates in units of standard cubic feet per hour according to methods set forth in § 98.234(b).{
