If the Gas to Oil Ratio (GOR) from each well is not available, the GOR from a cluster of wells in the same sub-basin category can be used. Additionally, if GOR cannot be determined from available data, one of the procedures specified in paragraph (g)(1)(vii)(A) or (B) of this section must be used to determine GOR. Furthermore, for oil wells where the gas production rate is not metered and Equation W–10A is used, the average gas production rate (PRs,p) can be calculated using Equation W–12C. The average GOR of all wells in an oil sub-basin should be reported in thousand standard cubic feet per barrel. If wildcat wells and/or delineation wells are the only wells that can be used for the measurement, the reporting of the gas to oil ratio can be delayed, but it must be reported by the specified date. The number of well completions that vented gas directly to the atmosphere without flaring should also be reported.{
