Yes, engineering calculations may be used for flare gas composition in equations W-19 through W-21 if the flared stream is a combination of gases from before and after the demethanizer as well as hydrocarbon product. The regulations allow for the use of representative composition from the source for the stream determined by engineering calculation based on process knowledge and best available data, especially when the stream going to the flare is a hydrocarbon product stream. Therefore, engineering calculations are a valid method for determining flare gas composition in the specified scenarios.{
